SoG-bloomcast -- Operational Forecasting of Spring Phytoplankton Blooms in the Strait of Georgia
Copyright 2011-2021 Doug Latornell and The University of British Columbia

This product includes software developed at
The Earth, Ocean, and Atmospheric Sciences Department of
The Univeristy of British Columbia (http://www.eos.ubc.ca).

To cite the SoG-bloomcast project please use the bibliographic information for one
or more of the following publications:

Latornell, D.J. and Allen, S.E.
Operational Prediction of the Strait of Georgia Spring Diatom Bloom.
Ocean Sciences Meeting, 2014.

Allen, S.E. and M.A. Wolfe.
Hindcast of the timing of the spring phytoplankton bloom in the Strait of Georgia, 1968-2010.
Progress in Oceanography. Volume 115, Pages 6-13, 2013.
http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.pocean.2013.05.026

Collins, A.K., S.E. Allen, and R. Pawlowicz.
The role of wind in determining the timing of the spring bloom in the Strait of Georgia.
Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, Volume 66, Pages 1597-1616, 2009.
http://www.nrcresearchpress.com/doi/abs/10.1139/f09-071
